whydpi (0.2.8-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Windows DNS: replaced the netsh/NRPT-based resolver override with a
    WinDivert packet-layer DNS hijacker — UDP/53 is intercepted at the
    driver, forwarded over DoH and answered with a synthetic reply.
    The OS's persistent DNS configuration is never mutated, so a
    crash or kill -9 can no longer leave the machine in a half-
    configured state, and DPI-injected "block-page" answers can no
    longer reach the browser.
  * DoH client: HTTP/1.1 keep-alive connection pool reduces per-query
    latency; mandatory TLS certificate/hostname verification plugs a
    MITM exposure that was documented but not previously enforced.
  * DoH: new TTL-aware in-memory DNS answer cache dedup-merges
    concurrent queries issued by browser parallel fetchers, so the
    first page load after the engine starts is no longer gated on a
    storm of duplicate round trips.
  * Discovery: new parallel strategy racing — on first connect to a
    previously-unseen SNI, multiple candidate fragmentations are tried
    concurrently and the winner cached.
  * Tray: new "Launch whyDPI on login" toggle (XDG autostart on Linux,
    Task Scheduler ONLOGON on Windows).  Visible menu entry renamed
    from "whyDPI Tray" to just "whyDPI".  New "Acceptable-use &
    disclaimer" menu item linking to DISCLAIMER.md.
  * Tray (pip install): self-provisions ~/.local/share/applications/
    on first launch, so the tray shows up in the KDE/GNOME launcher
    even without a .deb install.
  * Assets: canonical square assets/icon.png + horizontal
    assets/logo.png replace the previous logo-wide/logo-XX series;
    hicolor apps now install from icon-{sz}.png.
  * New top-level DISCLAIMER.md covering educational scope,
    acceptable-use boundaries, legal responsibility, privacy and
    export-control footnotes.

 -- byrdltd <byrdltd@users.noreply.github.com>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 08:00:00 +0000

whydpi (0.2.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Windows installer fixes: shellexec flag for post-install launch
    (fixes CreateProcess error 740 on "Finish") and the uninstaller's
    DNS-restore hook; whydpi.ui.tray / whydpi.cli are now correctly
    bundled into the PyInstaller onefile executables.
  * Linux: the tray now autostarts on login via an XDG autostart entry
    shipped in /etc/xdg/autostart/.  Previously users who installed the
    .deb saw no tray at all on first login and could not tell whether
    the service was active.
  * Linux: hicolor application icons (16–512px) are installed so the
    tray's Icon=whydpi renders at any panel size.
  * Linux: the tray fires a libnotify toast at startup and on every
    service state transition, so "is whyDPI actually running right
    now?" is answerable at a glance without hunting for a greyed vs.
    coloured panel indicator.

 -- byrdltd <byrdltd@users.noreply.github.com>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 09:00:00 +0000

whydpi (0.2.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Cross-platform tray: pystray-based system-tray icon for Linux
    (KDE/GNOME via AppIndicator) with state polling, polkit-escalated
    Start/Stop actions and state-dependent icon.
  * Windows port: packet-level TLS fragmenter via WinDivert with per-SNI
    strategy discovery that shares StrategyCache with the Linux engine;
    per-adapter DNS manager via netsh with crash-safe backup/restore.
    Ships as whydpi-tray.exe + whydpi.exe + a single Inno Setup
    installer, plus a Scoop bucket manifest so Windows users can do
    ``scoop install whydpi`` with zero account prompts.
  * Linux behaviour is byte-identical; no migration, no config changes.

